I"^<p>The Collingwood estate is one of five estates listed in <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MdX6GlaHDoBdG6CTsvjFaIuPtIa9id5O/view">Sutton’s Local Plan (2018)</a> for potential redevelopment:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonplan.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>It is also earmarked in Sutton’s <a href="http://sutton.addresscafe.com/app/exploreit/">Policy Map</a> as a potential renewal area:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonpolicymap.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>In 2013, the high-rise block on the estate was cladded with a light-blue ACU composite. In 2017, following the investigations as a result of the Grenfell disaster, it was <a href="https://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/news/15372936.we-feel-so-unsafe-sutton-tower-block-residents-at-balaam-house-say-they-are-living-in-fear-after-grenfell-to/">revealed</a> that the cladding had failed safety tests.</p>
